1 fertilizer material to the land based on the following:
2 (1) The nutrient content of the fertilizer material to be
3 applied.
4 (2) The fertility level of the soil.
5 (3) The nutrient needs of the current or planned crops.
6 (4) The nutrient holding capacity of the soil.
7 (5) Additional sources of nutrients, including legume credits,
8 process wastewater, or biosolids.
9 (6) Reasonable nitrogen losses.
10 (7) Reasonable phosphorus levels.
11 Sec. 4. "Ammonium nitrate" means the ammonium salt of nitric
12 acid, which must contain not less than thirty-three percent (33%)
13 nitrogen, fifty percent (50%) of which is in the ammonium form
14 and fifty percent (50%) of which is in the nitrate form.
