25 SECTION 43. IC 15-16-2.7 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
26 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
27 JULY 1, 2026]:
28 Chapter 2.7. Distributors and Users of Fertilizer Material for
29 Agricultural Crops
30 Sec. 1. (a) Nothing in this chapter impairs any authority granted
31 to the Indiana department of environmental management under
32 IC 13-13-5-1(1).
33 (b) Except as provided in subsection (c), this chapter applies to
34 any person that:
35 (1) uses; or
36 (2) distributes;
37 fertilizer material for the purposes of producing an agricultural
38 crop.
39 (c) This chapter does not apply to any person that uses or
40 distributes less than ten (10) cubic yards or four thousand (4,000)
41 gallons of fertilizer material in a calendar year.
42 (d) This chapter is in addition to any rules passed by the water
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

40
1 pollution control board regulating confined feeding operations. To
2 the extent that provisions of those rules require conditions or
3 actions that are more stringent than any of the provisions in this
4 chapter, operations that have a confined feeding operation or a
5 National Pollutant Discharge Elimination System (NPDES) permit
6 approval must comply with the more stringent provision.
7 Compliance with the more stringent provision satisfies the similar
8 requirement of this chapter.
9 Sec. 2. A person applying fertilizer material for the purposes of
10 producing an agricultural crop shall:
11 (1) develop a fertilizer application plan before applying
12 fertilizer material;
13 (2) apply fertilizer material in accordance with the fertilizer
14 application plan for the target application site;
15 (3) not apply fertilizer material directly to surface water;
16 (4) not apply fertilizer material to saturated ground; and
17 (5) not apply fertilizer material from a public road.
18 Sec. 3. (a) Unless there is a gradient barrier and a minimum
19 setback of ten (10) feet or a filter strip with a minimum width of
20 fifty (50) feet located between the application site and any of the
21 known features in the following table, a person shall apply
22 unmanipulated organic fertilizer according to the setback distances
23 as follows:
24 Unmanipulated Organic Fertilizer Application Setback Distances
25 (in feet)
26 Liquid –
27 Surface Application
28 Known Liquid – Liquid – < 6% >6%
29 Feature Injection Incorporation; Slope; Slope
30 or Surface or
