32 Incorporation (solid or Cover
33 (liquid/solid) compost); or
34 Surface
35 Application
36 to Pasture
37 Public 500 500 500 500
38 Water
39 Supply
40 Wells and
41 Surface
42 Intake
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

41
1 Surface 25 50 100 200
2 Waters
3 Sinkholes 25 50 100 200
4 Water 50 50 100 200
5 Wells
6 Drainage 5 50 100 200
7 Inlets
8 Property 0 10 50 50
9 Lines and
10 Public
11 Roads
12 (b) All setback distances described in the table under subsection
13 (a) shall be measured from the edge of the area of actual
14 application of unmanipulated organic fertilizer on the ground.
15 (c) The term "liquid incorporation", as used in the table under
16 subsection (a), means only unmanipulated organic fertilizer that
17 has been incorporated into the soil within twenty-four (24) hours
18 of application.
19 Sec. 4. A person may not apply unmanipulated organic fertilizer
20 to highly erodible land, unless the land has:
21 (1) at least forty percent (40%) crop residue; or
22 (2) a vegetative cover crop.
23 Sec. 5. (a) Except as provided in subsection (b), a person may
24 not apply unmanipulated organic fertilizer to frozen or snow
25 covered ground as follows:
26 (1) Within two hundred (200) feet of surface water.
27 (2) Within a floodway.
28 (3) In an amount that exceeds fifty percent (50%) of the
29 agronomic rate for the planned crop.
30 (4) With greater than two percent (2%) slope unless the
31 ground has:
32 (A) at least forty percent (40%) crop residue; or
33 (B) a vegetative cover crop.
34 (b) A person is not prohibited from applying unmanipulated
35 organic fertilizer under this section if the unmanipulated organic
36 fertilizer is applied by means of injection or same day
37 incorporation.
38 Sec. 6. A person who applies unmanipulated organic fertilizer
39 shall do the following:
40 (1) For the twenty-four (24) hour period immediately before
41 the application, monitor application site soil conditions and
42 the weather forecast for predicted rain events to ensure that
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

42
1 fertilizer runoff does not occur.
2 (2) During and immediately following the application,
3 monitor the application site effluent from field tile outlets and
4 surface water conveyance channels for a change of:
5 (A) color;
6 (B) flow; or
7 (C) volume.
8 (3) If there is a change to the effluent caused by the
9 application:
10 (A) stop the application immediately;
11 (B) stop or capture the effluent; and
12 (C) land apply or store the effluent.
13 Sec. 7. A person may not stage inorganic fertilizer as follows:
14 (1) Within three hundred (300) feet of:
15 (A) surface waters;
16 (B) drainage inlets; or
17 (C) water wells.
18 (2) In standing water, a waterway (as defined in
19 IC 13-11-2-265.2), or a floodway.
20 (3) For more than seventy-two (72) hours unless the fertilizer
21 is as follows:
22 (A) Covered with a tarpaulin or other suitable covering.
23 (B) Applied to a target field within thirty (30) days.
24 Sec. 8. (a) A person may not stage organic fertilizer:
25 (1) within three hundred (300) feet of surface waters, drainage
26 inlets, or water wells unless there is a:
27 (A) cover; or
28 (B) gradient barrier that contains or directs any organic
29 fertilizer away from the surface waters, drainage inlets,
30 and water wells;
31 (2) on an area with a slope greater than six percent (6%)
32 unless run-on and runoff are controlled; or
33 (3) on any standing water, waterway (as defined in
34 IC 13-11-2-265.2), or floodway.
35 (b) Organic fertilizer that is staged for more than seventy-two
36 (72) hours must be:
37 (1) protected by a:
38 (A) cover; or
39 (B) gradient barrier;
40 (2) applied within one hundred twenty (120) days;
41 (3) set back from property lines one hundred (100) feet;
42 (4) set back from public roads one hundred (100) feet; and
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

43
1 (5) set back from residential buildings four hundred (400)
2 feet.
3 Sec. 9. (a) A person required to be licensed under IC 15-16-2.5
4 that distributes organic fertilizer material as described in
5 IC 15-16-2.5-4 shall keep and maintain records of each
6 distribution.
7 (b) The records required under subsection (a) include the
8 following:
9 (1) The name of the certified applicator accepting receipt of
10 the organic fertilizer.
11 (2) The certification number of the certified applicator.
12 (3) The amount of fertilizer distributed.
13 (4) The representative nutrient value or values of the organic
14 fertilizer.
15 (5) The month, day, and year of distribution.
16 Sec. 10. (a) A person required to be licensed under IC 15-16-2.5
17 who applies:
18 (1) fertilizer material as described in IC 15-16-2.5-2; or
19 (2) organic fertilizer as described in IC 15-16-2.5-3;
20 must keep and maintain records of all fertilizer material and
21 organic fertilizer applications.
22 (b) The records required under subsection (a) must include the
23 following:
24 (1) The address or location description of the application site.
25 (2) The name of the certified applicator making or supervising
26 the application.
27 (3) The certification number of the certified applicator.
28 (4) The rate applied.
29 (5) The representative nutrient value or values of the fertilizer
30 material.
31 (6) The type of fertilizer material applied.
32 (7) The method of fertilizer application.
33 (8) The month, date, and year of application.
34 Sec. 11. All records required under this chapter must be:
35 (1) kept and maintained for two (2) years; and
36 (2) made available for inspection or copying within thirty (30)
37 days of written or oral request by the state chemist.
