20 a barrier layer that results in a downward water movement of not
21 greater than one-millionth of one centimeter per second (1.0 × 10-6
22 cm/sec) at construction and maintained at one hundred thousandth
23 of a centimeter per second (1.0 × 10-5 cm/sec) with a thickness of
24 not less than six (6) inches. The soil liner must be protected based
25 upon reliable engineering practices to maintain its integrity and
26 performance. If heavy mechanized equipment is to be moved over
27 the walls or floor liner, protection to the secondary containment
28 must be provided.
29 Sec. 20. (a) A liner is not required to be installed directly under
30 a storage container having a capacity of one hundred thousand
31 (100,000) gallons or more that has been constructed onsite and put
32 into use before July 6, 1991, if one (1) of the following alternative
33 procedures are complied with, certified to in writing by an official
