35 with the state chemist:
36 (1) Alternative 1 must meet the following requirements:
37 (A) A second bottom made of steel must be constructed for
38 the storage container and placed over the original bottom
39 and a layer of smooth, fine gravel or coarse sand having a
40 minimum thickness of six (6) inches.
41 (B) The original bottom of the storage container must be
42 tested for leaks before the sand layer or second bottom is
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

52
1 installed. A record of the test must be kept on file at the
2 storage facility.
3 (C) The newly constructed bottom must be tested for leaks
4 before any fluid fertilizer is stored on the newly
5 constructed bottom. A record of the test must be kept on
6 file at the storage facility or at the nearest local office from
