33 SECTION 51. IC 15-16-3.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
34 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
35 JULY 1, 2026]:
36 Chapter 3.5. Manure Based Fertilizer
37 Sec. 1. This chapter applies to any person that distributes
38 manure based fertilizers:
39 (1) in a bulk nonpackaged form and with a guaranteed
40 analysis;
41 (2) with a total nitrogen (N) content less than five percent
42 (5%); and
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

55
1 (3) with the summation of total nitrogen (N), available
2 phosphate (P O), and soluble potash (KO) content less than
2 5 2
3 ten percent (10%).
4 Sec. 2. (a) Before distributing manure based fertilizer in Indiana
5 for consideration, the person that is the guarantor of each brand
6 and grade of the manure based fertilizer must submit to the state
7 chemist:
8 (1) an application for registration on a form furnished by the
9 state chemist; and
10 (2) a filing fee of twenty dollars ($20).
11 (b) Upon approval of the application, the state chemist shall
12 furnish a copy of the registration to the applicant.
13 (c) All registrations expire on June 30 each year.
14 (d) In addition to the filing fee set forth in subsection (a), a late
15 filing fee equal to one hundred percent (100%) of the appropriate
16 filing fee is assessed when:
17 (1) an application to renew the registration of a manure based
18 fertilizer under this section is received after July 31; or
19 (2) a product that must be registered under this section is
20 found to be in distribution before registration.
21 (e) An application under subsection (a) must include the
22 following information:
23 (1) The name and address of the registrant.
24 (2) The brand and grade.
25 (3) The guaranteed analysis showing the minimum percentage
26 of plant food claimed in the following order and form:
27 (A) Total nitrogen (N) _____ percent.
28 (B) Available phosphate (P O) _____ percent.
2 5
29 (C) Soluble potash (KO) _____ percent.
2
30 (f) Additional plant food elements or other additives that are
31 determinable by chemical methods may be guaranteed only by
32 permission of the state chemist. The state chemist shall grant
33 permission only if the state chemist determines that the guarantee
34 would not constitute a misrepresentation and is correct. Additional
35 plant foods that are guaranteed:
36 (1) must be included in the guarantee in the form of the
37 element; and
38 (2) are subject to inspection and analysis in accordance with
39 the methods that the state chemist prescribes.
40 Sec. 3. Manure based fertilizer must be distributed with a
41 written or printed statement with the guaranteed analysis that:
42 (1) accompanies the manure based fertilizer at delivery; and
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

56
1 (2) is supplied to the purchaser at time of delivery.
2 Sec. 4. (a) A person that distributes manure based fertilizers in
3 Indiana to a person that is not a registrant or permit holder under
4 this chapter shall pay to the state chemist an inspection fee
5 computed under subsection (b).
6 (b) The inspection fee charged under subsection (a) is as follows:
7 (1) One hundred dollars ($100) for zero (0) tons up to one
8 thousand two hundred fifty (1,250) tons distributed per
9 reporting period.
10 (2) Five hundred dollars ($500) for more than one thousand
11 two hundred fifty (1,250) tons up to five thousand (5,000) tons
12 per reporting period.
13 (3) One thousand dollars ($1,000) for more than five thousand
14 (5,000) tons distributed per reporting period.
15 (c) Sales or exchanges between importers, manufacturers,
16 distributors, or registrants are exempt from the inspection fee.
17 Sec. 5. (a) Each registrant shall apply to the state chemist for a
18 permit to report the tonnage of manure based fertilizer sold and
19 pay the inspection fee as specified in section 4 of this chapter. In
20 making the application for the permit, the registrant must agree to
21 the following:
22 (1) To keep records that indicate accurately the tonnage and
23 kinds of manure based fertilizers sold in Indiana.
24 (2) To grant the state chemist permission to:
25 (A) examine the records required in subdivision (1); and
26 (B) verify the registrant's statement of tonnage.
27 (3) To report under oath to the state chemist on forms
28 furnished by the state chemist the tonnage of manure based
29 fertilizer sold during the period covered.
30 (b) The state chemist:
31 (1) may grant the permit to report tonnage if the state chemist
32 determines that the application of the permit to report
33 tonnage of manure based fertilizer described in subsection (a)
34 will lead to efficient enforcement of this chapter; and
35 (2) may revoke the permit to report tonnage at any time if it
36 appears to the state chemist that the registrant is not
37 complying with:
38 (A) the terms of the agreement entered into at the time of
39 the issuance of the permit; or
40 (B) this chapter.
41 (c) The report of tonnage is due and the inspection fees are
42 payable semiannually on the last day of the month following the
EH 1361—LS 7006/DI 150

57
1 end of the semiannual period.
2 (d) The state chemist may revoke the registrant's permit for any
3 of the following reasons:
4 (1) The report of tonnage is not filed and the inspection fee is
5 not paid by the fifteenth day following the due date.
6 (2) The report of tonnage is false.
7 (3) The permit holder has not complied with labeling
8 requirements of this chapter.
9 (e) If the inspection fee is unpaid after the fifteen (15) day grace
10 period described in subsection (d), a penalty must be assessed in
11 the amount of:
12 (1) fifty dollars ($50); or
13 (2) ten percent (10%) of the amount due;
14 whichever is greater, in addition to the amount due.
