1 Sec. 20. (a) The owner or operator of a storage structure shall
2 develop an emergency response plan to be kept in the operating
3 record. The plan must contain the following:
4 (1) Procedures for the following:
5 (A) Containing a processed manure release to prevent the
6 manure from reaching waters of the state.
7 (B) Locating the source of a processed manure release and
8 stopping the flow of manure.
9 (C) Returning released manure to the storage structure or
10 an approved waste management system.
11 (D) Contacting the following:
12 (i) The owner or operator.
13 (ii) Any applicable local emergency or health authorities.
14 (2) The names and telephone numbers of each person who is
15 identified by the owner or operator as responsible for
16 implementing the emergency response plan.
17 (3) Identification of areas where potential manure releases
18 could occur and their accompanying drainage points.
19 (4) Identification of equipment and cleanup materials to be
20 used in the event of a manure release.
21 (b) The owner or operator shall implement the emergency
22 response plan any time a processed manure release occurs. If
23 manure from the storage structure reaches waters of the state, the
24 owner or operator must do the following:
25 (1) Provide notification in accordance with the following:
26 (A) As soon as possible, but within two (2) hours of
27 discovery, communicate a spill report to the Indiana
28 department of environmental management, office of land
29 quality, emergency response section.
30 (B) If new or updated spill report information becomes
31 known that indicates a significant increase in the likelihood
32 of damage to the waters of the state, the responsible party
33 shall notify the Indiana department of environmental
34 management as soon as possible, but within two (2) hours
35 of the time the new or updated information becomes
36 known.
37 (2) If requested by the Indiana department of environmental
38 management, submit a written copy of the spill report to the
39 Indiana department of environmental management, office of
40 land quality, emergency response section.
41 (3) Except from modes of transportation other than pipelines,
42 exercise due diligence and document attempts to notify the
