4 Sec. 22. The state chemist shall adopt rules under IC 4-22-2:
5 (1) regulating the distribution of manure based fertilizer; and
6 (2) establishing fees for the distribution of manure based
7 fertilizer.
8 Sec. 23. (a) A person may not distribute a misbranded manure
9 based fertilizer. A manure based fertilizer is misbranded if:
10 (1) the manure based fertilizer carries any false or misleading
11 statement; or
12 (2) false or misleading statements concerning the manure
13 based fertilizer's nutrient value are made in any advertising
14 media accompanying or associated with the manure based
15 fertilizer.
16 (b) A person may not distribute an adulterated manure based
17 fertilizer. A manure based fertilizer is adulterated if:
18 (1) the manure based fertilizer contains any deleterious or
19 harmful substance in a sufficient amount to render the
20 manure based fertilizer injurious to beneficial plant life,
21 animals, humans, aquatic life, soil, or water when applied in
22 accordance with directions for use on the label; or
23 (2) the label of the manure based fertilizer does not include
24 adequate warning statements or directions for use that may
25 be necessary to protect plant life, animals, humans, aquatic
26 life, soil, or water.
27 Sec. 24. (a) The state chemist may:
28 (1) cancel the registration of any brand of manure based
29 fertilizer; or
30 (2) refuse to register any brand of manure based fertilizer
31 under this chapter;
32 if the state chemist receives satisfactory evidence that the
33 registrant has used fraudulent or deceptive practices in the evasion
34 or attempted evasion of this chapter.
35 (b) The state chemist may not revoke or refuse a registration
36 under subsection (a) until the registrant receives notice and has the
37 opportunity to appear for a hearing.
38 Sec. 25. (a) If the state chemist determines that a manure based
39 fertilizer is being offered for sale in violation of this chapter, the
40 state chemist may issue to and enforce upon the owner or
41 custodian:
42 (1) a written or printed stop sale, use, or removal order; and
